media.ext_alt_text: A comic with an alien girl describing how she has many ambitions and goals in life, but for some reason or another, can’t ever seem to pursue them. She can either overdo things or not start them at all.
The alien girl contemplates over how much she tries - how many calendars and journals she has filled but still doesn’t manage to make a routine or achieve her goals.

“It really feels like I have no power over my life. I can’t even shower or brush my hair. What if I’m just lazy?” The alien girl turns around and says to herself: “no. I’m not lazy. I’m not faking my ADHD, this is a real neurological issue. I will learn to understand my brain because I deserve to be more than a bystander to my own life.”
